replies.body:
Imo, assassins are just an unhealthy class in this game, especially with the way Riot designs them, notably their extremely high mobility coupled with their extremely high burst damage.

I do think Talon is a solid example of where assassins should be though. If he saves his ult to try to escape after blowing someone up, you can at least try to counter it with a pink ward/upgraded sweeper, so even though it can work as an escape it still has counterplay. Unfortunately for many assassins, they have the ability to jump in, delete someone, and disappear immediately without any potential for retaliation. Examples of this would be {{champion:7}} {{champion:238}} {{champion:245}} 

Playing against assassins is one of my least favorite things in this game if they know what theyre doing.
